		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Spend a few extra $$$, and get a universal device programmer, they're cheap on ebay:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://cgi.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?ViewItem&amp;item=220026695626">http://cgi.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?Vi ... 0026695626</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />I have one of these, it works fine, if you get the latest software. Can be unstable if it runs on just USB power.
<br />
<br />Programs a lot more than Willem, and is much much faster. Also you don't have to deal with dip switches anymore, yes!

		

